                        <div class="path-to-cert-content-summary">
                            <h2 class="section-heading"> Steps to Get a Microsoft Azure Administrator Certification </h2>
                            <p style="display:inline;">Getting a Microsoft Azure administrator certification is quite simple and can help shape your career in managing Azure cloud services. Strengthen your skills and knowledge of Azure administration, validate them by clearing the Microsoft Azure Administrator exam. Here’s how you can start:</p><span class="view-more-link">.....</span> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-more-link">View more</a>
                            <div class="view-more-data editor-content" id="path-to-cert-data" style="display:none;">
                                <p><b>1. Get Trained</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Check whether you meet the eligibility criteria for the Microsoft Azure Administrator Certification Exam. You need to have completed the Microsoft Azure Administrator Training with a Microsoft Learning Action Pack Partner like KnowledgeHut. Check out the available class schedules and choose one that best suits your requirements.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>2. Take the Exam</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>To be eligible to take the Microsoft Azure Administrator exam, candidates need to have expertise in implementing, managing, and monitoring an organization’s Microsoft Azure environment.</li>
                                    <li>Additionally, you need to have six months of hands-on experience administering Azure, and a strong understanding of core Azure services, Azure workloads, security, and governance.</li>
                                    <li>In addition, you need prior experience in using PowerShell, Azure CLI, Azure portal, and Azure Resource Manager templates.</li>
                                    <li>You can register with Microsoft and schedule an exam through their website and make a payment for US$ 165. Please note that the exam fees are subject to change as per Pearson Vue’s policies and it is best to check the latest, updated fees on their official website.</li>
                                    <li>You will clear the exam on obtaining a score of 700 or above.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Get Certified</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Hooray! You’re now a Microsoft Certified Azure Administrator. Flaunt your certification on your CV and your professional profiles.&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div> <a id="" href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-less-link hide">View Less</a>
